content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#"><gcmd:termsOfUse xmlns:gcmd="http://gcmd.gsfc.nasa.gov/">See http://gcmd.nasa.gov/r/l/TermsOfUse</gcmd:termsOfUse><gcmd:keywordVersion xmlns:gcmd="http://gcmd.gsfc.nasa.gov/">8.0</gcmd:keywordVersion><gcmd:schemeVersion xmlns:gcmd="http://gcmd.gsfc.nasa.gov/">2015-02-27 13:45:25</gcmd:schemeVersion> <skos:Concept rdf:about="0a4a7d30-32af-4e91-bbf5-a6381a6e8d22"    xml:base="http://gcmdservices.gsfc.nasa.gov/kms/concept/"    xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#">    <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="http://gcmdservices.gsfc.nasa.gov/kms/concepts/concept_scheme/projects"/>    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">SWAMP</skos:prefLabel>    <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Southwest Area Monsoon Project</skos:altLabel>    <skos:definition xml:lang="en"> South-West Area Monsoon Project (SWAMP) focuses on: -measurements of the central Arizona thunderstorm environments -examination of the monsoon structures and moistures fluxes -study of Mexican convective systems  For more information, link to "http://geography.asu.edu/aztc/swamp.html"  [Summary provided by Arizona University]   </skos:definition>    <skos:broader rdf:resource="4eb1894b-35b4-406b-8864-944a42bc7702"/> </skos:Concept> </rdf:RDF>
